TITLE: Florida thieves crash SUV into GameStop, flee with over $1,000 in merchandise
SUMMARY: Florida police are asking for the public's help finding out who crashed an SUV into a GameStop location and fled with over $1,000 worth of merchandise.

TITLE: Two arrested at NYC councilman's apartment in 'gays against groomers' protest over Drag Queen Story Hour
SUMMARY: New York City Councilman Erik Bottcher said two protesters who came to his apartment building angry over Drag Queen Story Hour and gained entry were arrested for trespassing.

TITLE: Crime in Georgia town hits 'new low' after someone steals 'the baby Jesus right before Christmas,' police say
SUMMARY: Georgia police on Tybee Island are investigating the theft of Nativity scene statues from outside a church. Police said stealing "baby Jesus right before Christmas is a new low."

TITLE: Mystery NV fossil site may have been a 'maternity ward' for giant marine mammals
SUMMARY: Scientists have uncovered new clues that suggest a fossil site in Nevada may actually be a marine maternity ward. Previously, many thought the site was a massive graveyard.

TITLE: Maricopa County seeks new animal shelter director
SUMMARY: Arizona’s Animal Care and Control is seeking a new director to oversee animal shelters for a month amid rising number of strays and slow pet adoption.

TITLE: Louisiana’s secretary of state bans TikTok on devices issued by Department of State
SUMMARY: Louisiana’s secretary of state said Monday that TikTok will be banned on all devices issued by the Department of State. He believes that this will protect U.S. data from begin accessed.

TITLE: Man pleads guilty to manslaughter after shaking, throwing 3-year-old girl
SUMMARY: A Nevada man has pleaded guilty to involuntary manslaughter. The man, who was babysitting his girlfriend’s daughter, shook and threw the 3-year-old.

TITLE: Nazi symbols carved into a Hanukkah menorah in CA, suspect arrested
SUMMARY: Eric Brian King, of Dallas, was arrested for allegedly carving Nazi symbols into a menorah, a candelabrum used during the Jewish holiday of Hanukkah.

TITLE: MN man fatally shoots his fiancée and cousin, then kills himself in AZ
SUMMARY: A Minnesota man killed himself after fatally shooting his fiancée and cousin. However, officials said they do not know why the man shot the two.

TITLE: Idaho murders: Police investigate abandoned white Hyundai found in Oregon
SUMMARY: Moscow police are probing an unoccupied white Hyundai in Eugene, Oregon, in connection to the quadruple homicide near the University of Idaho campus, a spokeswoman confirmed.
